(A. Architecture Overview) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 628.25 Tm
(fun.lol is implemented as a lightweight single-page web application with a Node.js backend. The) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 614.75 Tm
(frontend is delivered from static files and switches between an authenticated dashboard, a) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 601.25 Tm
(bio/profile editor, public profile pages, games, friends, tribes, and tribe chats. The backend) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 587.75 Tm
(exposes JSON API routes for authentication, profile publishing, media delivery, friends, tribes,) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 574.25 Tm
(tribe chat, and the server-backed Snake score.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 557.75 Tm
(Confirmed implementation:) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 541.25 Tm
(- Frontend files: `index.html`, `script.js`, and `styles.css`.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 527.75 Tm
(- Backend entry point: `server.js`, using Node's built-in `http` module rather than Express or) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 514.25 Tm
(another framework.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 500.75 Tm
(- Static routing: `/` serves `index.html`; `/u/:handle` also serves `index.html` so the client can) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 487.25 Tm
(load a public profile by handle.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 473.75 Tm
(- API routing: `/api/...` routes are handled directly in `server.js`.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 460.25 Tm
(- Local persistence fallback: `data/users.json` and `data/profiles.json`.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 446.75 Tm
(- Optional Supabase persistence: enabled when `SUPABASE_URL` and `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` are) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 433.25 Tm
(present.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 419.75 Tm
(- Supabase tables currently defined in `supabase-schema.sql`: `app_users`, `app_sessions`, and) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 406.25 Tm
(`app_profiles`.) Tj
